1 SECTION 1. Section 461-1, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
2 amended by amending the definition of "registered pharmacy
3 technician" to read as follows:
4 ""Registered pharmacy technician" means a person, exclusive
5 of pharmacy interns and auxiliary pharmacy personnel, who is at
6 least sixteen years of age with a certificate of registration
7 issued by the board pursuant to section 461-9.5, and who may, in
8 addition to the tasks of an auxiliary pharmacy personnel,
9 perform filling, packaging, manipulative, repetitive, or other
10 nondiscretionary tasks [7—aftd-^feae4ts—speei-fied—ift—seetieft—4-&1—
11 11.4,] only while assisting and while under the supervision and
12 control of a registered pharmacist[—]; provided that to
13 administer vaccinations, the registered pharmacy technician
14 shall be at least eighteen years of age and meet the
15 requirements under section 461-11.4."
